LTC0_RNG4_DRNG_HASH_CONTROL.description: LTC RNG4 DRNG Hash Control Register

LTC0_RNG4_DRNG_HASH_DIGEST.description: LTC RNG4 DRNG Hash Digest Register

ENC.description: Encrypt/Decrypt. This bit selects encryption or decryption.

ICV_TEST.description: ICV Checking / Test AES fault detection

ALG.description: Algorithm. This field specifies which algorithm is being selected.
Algorithm. This field specifies which algorithm is being selected.

KS.description: Key Size. This is the size of a Key measured in bytes

AES.description: Reset AESA. Writing a 1 to this bit resets the AES Accelerator core engine.

DES.description: Reset DESA. Writing a 1 to this bit resets the DES Accelerator.

PK.description: Reset PKHA. Writing a 1 to this bit resets the Public Key Hardware Accelerator.

IM.description: Interrupt Mask. Once this bit is set, it can only be cleared by hard reset.

IFS.description: Input FIFO Byte Swap. Byte swap all data that is written to the Input FIFO.

OFS.description: Output FIFO Byte Swap. Byte swap all data that is read from the Onput FIFO.

CM.description: Clear the Mode Register. Writing a one to this bit causes the Mode Register to be cleared.

CICV.description: Clear the ICV Size Register. Writing a one to this bit causes the ICV Size Register to be cleared.

CCR.description: Clear the Context Register. Writing a one to this bit causes the Context Register to be cleared.

CPKA.description: Clear the PKHA A Size Register

CPKB.description: Clear the PKHA B Size Register

CPKN.description: Clear the PKHA N Size Register

CPKE.description: Clear the PKHA E Size Register

COF.description: Clear Output FIFO. Writing a 1 to this bit causes the Output FIFO to be cleared.

CIF.description: Clear Input FIFO. Writing a 1 to this bit causes the Input Data FIFO.

CL1.description: algorithms. The algorithms field indicates which algorithm is asserting an error. Others reserved

AL.description: AAD Last. Only AAD data will be written into the Input FIFO.

IL.description: IV Last. Only IV data will be written into the Input FIFO.

PKASZ.description: PKHA A Size. This is the size of the numeric value, in bytes, contained within the PKHA A Register.

PKBSZ.description: PKHA B Size. This is the size of the numeric value, in bytes, contained within the PKHA B Register.

PKNSZ.description: PKHA N Size. This is the size of the numeric value, in bytes, contained within the PKHA N Register.

PKESZ.description: PKHA E Size. This is the size of the numeric value, in bytes, contained within the PKHA E Register.

IF0.description: Instantiated Flag 0. State Handle 0 has been instantiated.

IF1.description: Instantiated Flag 1. State Handle 1 has been instantiated.

TF0.description: Test Flag State Handle 0. State Handle 0 has been instantiated as a test (deterministic) instance.

TF1.description: Test Flag State Handle 1. State Handle 1 has been instantiated as a test (deterministic) instance.

RESINT0.description: This read-only register holds the Reseed Interval for State Handle 0.

RESINT1.description: This read-only register holds the Reseed Interval for State Handle 1.

HD.description: Hashing Done. This bit asserts when the hashing engine is done.

HB.description: Hashing Begin. Writing this bit will cause the Hashing Engine to begin hashing.

HI.description: Hashing Initialize. Writing this bit will initialize the Hashing Engine.

HTM.description: Hashing Test Mode. Writing this bit will put RNG in Hashing Test Mode.

HTC.description: Hashing Test Mode Clear. Writing this bit will take the RNG out of hashing test mode.

HASHBUF.description: This write-only register provides access to the internal SHA-256 hashing engine's 64-byte buffer

IFL.description: Input FIFO Level. These bits indicate the current number of entries in the Input FIFO.

IFF.description: Input FIFO Full. The Input FIFO is full and should not be written to.

OFL.description: Output FIFO Level. These bits indicate the current number of entries in the Output FIFO.

OFF.description: Output FIFO Full. The Output FIFO is full and should not be written to.

GPCNT0_VAL.description: General Purpose Counter 0 Timeout Value Register

INV_CRC_VAL.description: Invert bits in the CRC Output Value

CRC_OUT_FLIP.description: CRC Output Value Bit Reversal or Flip

CRC_IN_FLIP.description: CRC Input Byte's Bit Reversal or Flip Control

GPCNT0_IM.description: General Purpose Timer 0 Timeout Interrupt Mask
